s. 48.
     (2)     The amount of BTR special land tax payable by the owner of land in
respect of a relevant year is the amount determined using the
formula&#8212;
where&#8212;
          SL     is the BTR special land tax assessed for the owner of the land
in respect of the relevant year;
          T     is the taxable value of the relevant land in the relevant
year;
          t     is the number of the tax year in respect of which the BTR special
land tax is being determined, calculated from the first year of benefit until
the relevant year;
          BR     is the benefit rate of&#8212;
         (a)     if the owner of land is an absentee owner and the relevant year
